    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; 5 Engine Service Manual - Rear Cover and Flywheel - Removal</stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>Removal</title>
        <svcsubsecinfo>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To prevent personal injury or death, read all safety instructions in the "Safety Information"
                        section of this manual.
                    </para>
                </warning>
                <warning>
                    <para>To prevent personal injury or death, shift transmission to park or neutral, set parking brake,
                        and block wheels before doing diagnostic or service procedures.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To prevent personal injury or death, disconnect ground (-) cable from battery before doing
                        service or diagnostic procedures.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To prevent personal injury or death, use a suitable lifting device to support the transmission
                        assembly during removal and installation.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To prevent personal injury or death, support engine (if in chassis) before removing any engine
                        mounting bracket or flywheel housing bolts.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To prevent personal injury or death, wear safety glasses with side shields. Limit compressed
                        air pressure to 207 kPa (30 psi).
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
        </svcsubsecinfo>
        <svcproc id="s26513.1.2" svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="4">
            <title>Flywheel</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">
                    <hotlnk document="eges390_301.xml" xrefid="s1206">Measure ring gear runout</hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="s1206"/>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="e3001401.3" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figJ06/J06071.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>Transmission adapter ring bolt removal (stripped chassis)</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Stripped chassis applications, remove 12 bolts (M10 x 35) securing the transmission
                    adapter ring to the rear cover.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="e3001402" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figJ06/J06010.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>Flywheel bolts (typical)</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove and discard 10 flywheel mounting bolts (M10 x 31 - CityStar&#8482;) (M10 x 77 -
                    stripped chassis).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove flywheel assembly.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="e3001404" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figJ06/J06014.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>Flywheel adapter removal (CityStar&#8482;)</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Rear cover bolt head locations</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Placement of the heel bar</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>(CityStar&#8482; applications only) - To prevent engine damage, place a heel bar onto the head
                        of a rear cover bolt to remove the flywheel adapter. This will prevent cracking the aluminum
                        rear cover.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>To prevent engine damage, carefully remove and store flywheel adapter or adapter hub. Damage
                        to the adapter sealing surface can result in a rear oil seal leak.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">For CityStar&#8482; applications only, place a heel bar on the head of the rear cover
                    bolt and the hook under the lip of the flywheel adapter. Alternate between the two rear cover head
                    bolts to pry off the flywheel adapter.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="e3001405" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figJ06/J06015.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>Flywheel adapter removed (CityStar&#8482;)</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Dowel pin</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Pin recess</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Dust seal lip surface</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcproc>
